===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|ic}} – a tied bag ({{zh-l|*𣒚}}), with various items in it ({{zh-l|*𤕦}}). {{och-l|𤕦}} also serves as a phonetic element. There are many alternative forms. In the modern, standard form, the bottom turned into an abbreviated form of {{zh-l|*襄}}, with the result that the character is a {{Han compound|㯻|襄|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=bag|abb1=y|abb2=y|nocap=y}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|ss=𰀉|alt=𬺿,嚢,𡄜,𢑿,𣡦,𣡪,𧛦,𣡏}}
Possibly {{der|zh|sit}}; compare {{cog|my|နွှင်||to skin; to peel off}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

